com.tsgrp.migration.event

Class JDBCQueryListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.event.JDBCQueryListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PostUpdateLogItemEventListener, SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener, TargetEndImportNodeEventListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JDBCBatchRunNumberListener, PortalNodeJdbcLogWriterListener, RepeatingJDBCQueryListener

    public class JDBCQueryListener
extends AbstractListener
implements SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener, TargetEndImportNodeEventListener, PostUpdateLogItemEventListener
    Execute a single query for the current Node, optionally including node attributes as query parameters and optionally binding results to the Node. For handling repetating attributes in a multi-query fashion, see RepeatingJDBCQueryListener NOTE: This class is JDK 1.4 compatible so that it can be used as-is in projects that cannot use Java 5 or newer (basically, the FileNet projects).

      • setBindResultsToNode

        public void setBindResultsToNode(boolean value)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. Boolean indicating whether or not values returned by query should be stored as attributes on the node. If bindResultsToNode is set to true, the injected query must be a READ query. If bindResultsToNode is set to false, the injected query must be an UPDATE query.
        Parameters:
        value -

      • setRunQueryOnAssociationNodes

        public void setRunQueryOnAssociationNodes(boolean runQueryOnAssociationNodes)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. Boolean indicating whether or not to run the query on all association nodes If set to true each association node will build and run the query If set to false the query will only run for the main node Defaults to false
        Parameters:
        runQueryOnAssociationNodes - - boolean controlling whether to run query for all association nodes.

      • setRepeatingBehavior

        public void setRepeatingBehavior(java.lang.String value)
